titleInfo.title: (PS) Flowers v. County of Sacramento et al
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER signed by Magistrate Judge Kendall J. Newman on 5/8/2013. Defense counsel shall continue to endeavor in good faith to contact plaintiff. In the event that defense counsel is unable to reach plaintiff within 60 days of the date of Order, counsel shall file another Notice of Status of Settlement. It shall include a signed Declaration describing efforts made to contact plaintiff. Pursuant to defendants 45 Notice of Settlement, and finding good cause therefore, Magistrate Judge Newman hereby gives parties an additional 60 days from date of this Order to submit dispositional documents. (Marciel, M)

titleInfo.title: (PS) Flowers v. County of Sacramento et al
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER signed by Magistrate Judge Kendall J. Newman on 9/19/2013 ORDERING 49 Pursuant to defendants' request, and finding good cause therefore, the undersigned hereby gives the parties a final EXTENSION of 60 days from the date of this order to submit dispositional documents. If the MSPRC does not respond to plaintiff's letter within 60 days from the date of this order, the parties shall file a proposed order explaining as much and directing defendants to issue a single payment in the amount of $3,500.00, made payable to both plaintiff and Medicare, and shall order plaintiff to resolve the Medicare lien with MSPRC.(Reader, L)
